main event: A blinking object in the sky was reported by numerous callers to the University of Minnesota, which was later identified as the star Capella.
interesting points: The object was described as a red, bright light that appeared to have a 'down bouncing motion'.
The University of Minnesota received numerous calls about the blinking object in the same location.
The object was identified as the star Capella.
The report indicates that the sighting was 'probable astronomical' in nature.
sighted object: A blinking, red and bright light in the sky
witnesses: Numerous callers to the University of Minnesota
photographs: No photographs included in the report
